news.title: U.S. home builder sentiment plunges, services activity in New York region stalls
news.para: The National Association of Home Builders/Wells Fargo Housing Market Index fell for a seventh straight month to 55, the lowest level since May 2020, from 67 in June, NAHB said in a statement on Monday.

news.title: Shimao Group says receives resumption guidance from Hong Kong stock exchange
news.para: Trading in the shares was suspended on April 1 after the Shanghai-based developer failed to publish its 2021 financial results before the regulatory deadline.

news.title: Fitch cuts China's Guangzhou R&F Properties to 'restricted default'
news.para: R&F received consent from its creditors to extend maturities for $4.9 billion worth of offshore bonds, the latest such move by a Chinese developer to avoid default.

news.title: TCS setting up eight new office spaces that can seat 10,000 staffers each
news.para: They are planned in line with the company’s 25 by 25 model that entails having only 25% of the workforce working from offices for 25% of the time by 2025.

news.title: CBI to produce DHFL's former MD & director in court in Rs 34,815 crore scam case
news.para: The CBI will seek Wadhawans' custody in connection with its FIR related to the scam, they said. Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan were in Lucknow in connection with the PF scam also probed by the agency, they said.

news.title: Chennai development body issues lock and seal notices to 720 buildings
news.para: Of these, only 5 percent have carried out rectifications and only one building with violations hgas been demolished. At least 50% of them have gone for appeals and sought time to make rectifications while the rest have not responded to the notice.

news.title: Not verbal, only written pact valid in property purchase: Assam REAT
news.para: Delivering a judgement, Assam REAT Chairperson Justice (Retd) Manojit Bhuyan and Member Onkar Kedia said the terms and conditions of a written contract cannot be modified by any oral agreement.

news.title: Bengaluru development body asks for affidavits from plot owners seeking plan approval
news.para: The move of the developer, Bangalore Development Authority (BDA), comes in the wake of its failure to complete civil works, underground drainage, water supply and electrification works in the layout.

news.title: Ondipudur residents seek patta to construct houses
news.para: Submitting a petition at the weekly grievance redressal meeting in the district collectorate, the petitioners said the district administration surveyed land parcels to issue pattas in 2015, but nothing happened after that.

news.title: Noida metro rail corporation to give out commercial space at four metro stations
news.para: The Noida Metro Rail Corporation (NMRC) said in the request for proposal (RFP) document that the objective is to make use of real estate value to get additional revenue other than the existing earnings through Metro fares.

news.title: Chandigarh: Property tax relief for colonies may be scuttled
news.para: ​However, with the Chandigarh administration dragging its feet on a decision, the proposed relief may not come to pass. Sources confirmed that the UT has been making queries from the MC in this regard.

news.title: SCDRC orders Aliens Space Station's builder to pay Rs 65 lakh to three flat buyers
news.para: The realty firm had promised to build a huge apartment complex ‘Aliens Space Station’ at Tellapur in Medak district in 2008.

news.title: Noida: RG Residency residents rally against AOA, seek fresh polls
news.para: According to the residents, the current AOA executive body was formed without any general body meeting. But, the AOA refuted the allegations as false and asserted that they have been fighting for the overall benefit of the housing society.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses to stay eviction of occupants from nine illegal buildings in Thane
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice M S Karnik said it did not want citizens to live a life fraught with the risk of their buildings collapsing during the rains.

news.title: Structural audit of high rise, two-decade old buildings priority: Delhi government to HC
news.para: ​The state government said it had been decided in a meeting chaired by the chief secretary that quality and calculation test checks may be carried out on a sample basis in respect of high-rise private and government buildings having high footfall or occupancy by the concerned local bodies.
